ax width\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" style=\"width:48%; text-align:center;\"|Summary\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|storm}}\" | EF0\n|WNW of [[Cave Spring, Georgia|Cave Spring]]\n|[[Floyd County, Georgia|Floyd]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|34.1239|-85.3675|name=Cave Spring (Apr 13, EF0)}}\n|04:31\u201304:32\n|{{convert|0.5|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|50|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|Several trees were downed and large tree limbs were broken off by a brief tornado.<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|storm}}\" | EF0\n|N of [[Lindale, Georgia|Lindale]] to W of [[Rome, Georgia|Rome]]\n|[[Floyd County, Georgia|Floyd]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|34.1924|-85.1735|name=Lindale (Apr 13, EF0)}}\n|04:42\u201304:45\n|{{convert|3.2|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|50|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n| A brief tornado downed multiple trees, some of which fell on power lines.<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|cat1}}\" | EF1\n|WSW of [[Cartersville, Georgia|Cartersville]] to E of [[White, Georgia|White]]\n|[[Bartow County, Georgia|Bartow]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|34.1492|-84.82855|name=Cartersville (Apr 13, EF1)}}\n|05:06\u201305:21\n|{{convert|13|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|250|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|1 death \u2013 A tornado touched down west-southwest of Cartersville and caused minor damage to a small business and downed fences. In southwestern Cartersville, a large oak tree fell on a house, killing the sleeping occupant. Sporadic tree damage continued thereafter until it reached Bells Ferry Road where numerous trees were snapped or uprooted and one home was damaged. The tornado continued into the Pine Log Wildlife Management Area where 60\u201370 trees were downed before it dissipated. Two people were injured along its path.<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|cat1}}\" | EF1\n|SSW of [[Salacoa Valley, Georgia|Salacoa Valley]]\n|[[Cherokee 