 continued into the Pine Log Wildlife Management Area where 60\u201370 trees were downed before it dissipated. Two people were injured along its path.<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|cat1}}\" | EF1\n|SSW of [[Salacoa Valley, Georgia|Salacoa Valley]]\n|[[Cherokee County, Georgia|Cherokee]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|34.3524|-84.6028|name=Salacoa Valley (Apr 13, EF1)}}\n|05:32\u201305:33\n|{{convert|0.71|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|100|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|This tornado regenerated from the 05:06&nbsp;UTC Bartow County tornado. Around 250 to 300 trees were downed northwest of [[Waleska, Georgia|Waleska]].<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|storm}}\" | EF0\n|NW of [[Waverly Hall, Georgia|Waverly Hall]]\n|[[Harris County, Georgia|Harris]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|32.7279|-84.7294|name=Waverly Hall (Apr 13, EF0)}}\n|05:53\u201305:55\n|{{convert|3|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|50|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|Several trees in a remote and forested area were downed.<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|storm}}\" | EF0\n|NW of [[Woodland, Georgia|Woodland]]\n|[[Talbot County, Georgia|Talbot]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|32.7516|-84.5144|name=Woodland (Apr 13, EF0)}}\n|06:08\u201306:10\n|{{convert|2.9|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|100|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|Trees downed by the tornado blocked several roads.<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|cat3}}\" | EF3\n|S of [[Thomaston, Georgia|Thomaston]] to NW of [[Redbone, Georgia|Redbone]]\n|[[Upson County, Georgia|Upson]], [[Lamar County, Georgia|Lamar]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|32.8496|-84.3335|name=Thomaston (Apr 13, EF3)}}\n|06:19\u201306:35\n|{{convert|16.7|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|1200|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|A tornado touched down just south of Thomaston and traveled northeast. It steadily intensified and grew in diameter as it approached Trice Cemetery Road. There, a mobile home was rolled and rotated 90\u00b0. Farther northeast, one home had the majority of its roof torn off and nearly all trees within {{convert|220|yd|m|abbr=on}} of it were snapped. The National Weather Service's WSR-88D radar detected debris lofted up to {{convert|25000|ft|m|abbr=on}} at this time. Thereafter, the tornado weakened and ultimately dissipated shortly after crossing into Lamar County. A total of 159&nbsp;structures were affected by the tornado; 7 were destroyed, 20 had major damage, and 38 had minor damage.<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|storm}}\" | EF0\n|NNE of [[Union City, Georgia|Union City]]\n|[[Fulton County, Georgia|Fulton]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|33.6288|-84.5263|name=Union City (Apr 13, EF0)}}\n|06:36\u201306:39\n|{{convert|2.75|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|50|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|A short-lived tornado snapped or uprooted many trees; debris was detected by the local NWS's radar up to {{convert|1000|ft|m|abbr=on}}.<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|cat3}}\" | EF3\n|SW of [[Collier, Georgia|Collier]] to NNW of [[Forsyth, Georgia|Forsyth]]\n|[[Monroe County, Georgia|Monroe]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|33.0928|-84.033|name=Forsyth (Apr 13, EF3)}}\n|06:40\u201306:47\n|{{convert|5.3|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|300|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|This tornado regenerated from the 06:19&nbsp;UTC Upson/Lamar County tornado. The tornado initially touched down southwest of Collier and quickly intensified as it approached Highway 41. There, a large metal building and small home were completely destroyed. The metal frame and concrete footers of the former structure were ripped from the ground, leaving behind a concrete slab. The occupant of the small home was injured. Several vehicles, a small plane, a tractor, and a boat were flipped near the structures. NWS radar detected debris up to {{convert|19000|ft|m|a